        <coverage>
            <geographicCoverage>
                <geographicDescription>The Fosen peninsula is north west of Trondheim in Central Norway. Bjugn municipality is located in the west of the peninsula. The peninsula consists of numerous valleys and mountains reaching about 500-600 m a.s.l., incised by several fjords. Spruce is established on most of the available sites with suitable soils in the interior region. The timberline is usually made up of conifers. Wooded areas along the northwestern coast are mostly covered by birch and other unexacting decidious trees.</geographicDescription>
